        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 25 at 2:17PM CST by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 217 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lake View, or 11 miles southwest of Bessemer, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hoover, Alabaster, Bessemer, Pelham, Helena, Indian Springs Village,
Lake View, North Johns, Tannehill Ironworks State Park, Abernant,
Bluff Park, Oak Mountain Amphitheater, Splash Adventure, Riverchase,
Patton Creek, Hoover Metropolitan Stadium, Ross Bridge, Riverchase
Galleria, Oak Mountain State Park, and North Bibb.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 600 PM CST for central and
west central Alabama.</instruction>
